channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: California's proposed parental notification policy for gender identity changes fails to qualify for ballot
item.description: A policy that would have required California schools to notify parents if their child wants to change their gender identity failed to qualify as a ballot measure.

item.title: Trump Jury to Enter Deliberations Phase Wednesday
item.description: Jury deliberations in Donald Trump 's criminal hush money trial are expected to begin Wednesday after the panel receives instructions from the judge on the law governing the case and what they can take into account in evaluating the case.

item.title: POLL: 54% of Dems Would Be A-OK With Biden Being Jettisoned From Presidential Ticket
Top adviser to Dem Senate candidate posted photo with religious leader who compared Jews to termites
item.description: A top adviser to a House Democrat running for Senate in Michigan once posted on social media about supporting an event featuring Farrakhan and the Nation of Islam.

item.title: Fmr Trump Attorney Ellis Disbarred for 3 Years in Colorado
item.description: Jenna Ellis, a former attorney for former President Donald Trump, has been disbarred from practicing law in Colorado for three years following her guilty plea in the 2020 Georgia election interference case brought by Democrat Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis.

item.title: IDF: 'Small' Munitions Used in Deadly Rafah Strike Could Not Have Caused Such Devastation by Themselves
'Kind of scary': Controversial medical procedure may soon be legal in another blue state
item.description: Lawmakers are rallying support in another blue state to pass the proposed Medical Aid in Dying Act, and one Democratic lawmaker says there is an "excellent chance" of it passing.

item.title: Gov. Noem to Newsmax: Feds Not Protecting S.D. Tribes
item.description: South Dakota Republican Gov. Kristi Noem told Newsmax on Tuesday that Mexican cartels have found a "safe haven" in her state's tribal territories, bringing violence, human trafficking, and drugs, and she's powerless to do anything about it.

NY v. Trump: Judge Merchan to present jury with instructions ahead of deliberations
item.description: The framework a Manhattan jury will use to consider the charges against former President Trump and reach a verdict will be revealed by Judge Juan Merchan on Wednesday.

item.title: Louisiana to Require Schools to Post Ten Commandments
item.description: Louisiana's legislature has passed a bill requiring all public schools to display the Ten Commandments.

item.title: WATCH: Even CNN Doesn't Think Prosecution Has Proven Case Against Trump
Trump strategy: Hitting blue areas, courting minorities and unfriendly audiences
item.description: Former President Trump is seemingly using an unorthodox strategy in his general election campaign: targeting deep-blue areas often considered hostile territory by fellow Republicans.

item.title: Criminal Illegal Alien Charged With Murder
item.description: An illegal alien who was charged with murdering a West Virginia woman earlier this month had spent over two decades in prison in El Salvador before getting released into the U.S. under President Joe Biden.
